[2026-06-11T04:08:52.470Z] [THINK]
The user is asking whether `--symlink-install` is needed.

`--symlink-install` creates symbolic
[/THINK]
[2026-06-11T04:08:52.918Z] [THINK]
 links to source files instead of copying them during install. This means if you modify Python files (
[/THINK]
[2026-06-11T04:08:53.357Z] [THINK]
like launch files), you don't need to re-run `colcon build` at all — the symlink points directly to the source.

Without `--symlink-inst
[/THINK]
[2026-06-11T04:08:53.765Z] [THINK]
all`, every time you change a launch.py or any installable file, you need `colcon build` to
